  "text": "Here we are regarding the 2-point and 3-point vertices as elements of H * ⊗ H * and H * ⊗ H * ⊗ H * , i.e., as bilinear and trilinear functionals on the state space H = ⊕ ij H ij . These properties are an immediate consequence of the fact that Q S is the zero-mode of a conserved current. They are easily proved by contour deformations on the 2-and 3-punctured disks that define the vertices (see e.g. [CITATION_1] ).",
